        "subject": "LU-4971 ldlm: wait for the connection to be established",
        "message": "LU-4971 ldlm: wait for the connection to be established\n\nConsider the following race condition:\n\n1) There are two MDTs in the system, when the client mount,\n   it will trigger MDS_CONNECT request to each of the MDT.\n   But the connection RPC will be handled asynchronously.\n   The mount processing will go ahead when the connection\n   between the client and MDT0 is established, but will\n   not wait for the connection between the client and the\n   MDT1 to be established.\n\n2) After the client mount returned, the application tries\n   to \"stat $MOUNT/a/b\", the directory \"a\" resides on the\n   MDT0, the \"b\" resides on the MDT1. So the client will\n   send lock_enqueue RPC to the MDT0 firstly.\n\n3) The RPC handler on the MDT0 finds that the target object\n   \"b\" resides on the remote MDT1, then it replies the client\n   to try to talk with the MDT1.\n\n4) The client gets the MDT0's reply, then forwards the request\n   to the MDT1 via MDC1, but at that time, the connection between\n   the client and the MDT1 has not been established yet.\n\n5) For most of other RPCs, above case is not a problem, because\n   the client-side RPC sender (in ptlrpc) will handle kinds of\n   connection issues. But for the ldlm_enqueue request, it is\n   somewhat different, because before giving the ldlm_enqueue RPC\n   to the sender (or to the ptlrpc), the sponsor will check the\n   export connect flags that will not be set until the connection\n   between the client and the MDT has been established. So at such\n   time point, the sponsor of the ldlm_enqueue request will get \"0\"\n   flags from the export connection flags, then trigger the ASSERTION.\n\nThis patch will make the ldlm_enqueue request sponsor to wait until\nthe connection between the client and the server has been established.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I104faded1ea1652c769e6fc775e3c7b0d52c10cd\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
